# tunan — Engineering Workflow Toolkit

You have access to the **tunan** plugin, a suite of AI-powered development tools that make each unit of engineering work easier than the last. The plugin bundles 43 agents, 66 skills, and 4 MCP servers.

## Core Workflow

tunan provides a structured engineering pipeline:

1. **`/tunan:brainstorm`** — Explore requirements and approaches through collaborative dialogue, then capture a right-sized requirement as a GitHub issue.
2. **`/tunan:plan`** — Create structured implementation plans stored on the feature issue.
3. **`/tunan:work`** — Execute work efficiently while maintaining quality and finishing features.
4. **`/tunan:code-review`** — Structured code review using tiered persona agents.
5. **`/tunan:verify`** — Run test/lint/build checks and emit a validation contract.
6. **`/tunan:compound`** — Document solved problems to compound team knowledge.

## Skills Reference

The full skill library lives under `plugins/skills/`. When a user invokes a tunan workflow, load the corresponding `SKILL.md` from the skill directory and follow its instructions.

