## MCP Servers

The plugin bundles 4 MCP servers configured in `.mcp.json`:
- **github** — GitHub API integration (issues, PRs, code search)
- **gemini-search** — Google AI-powered web search
- **sequential-thinking** — Structured problem-solving
- **playwright** — Browser automation (if installed)

## Artifact Model

All durable artifacts live as GitHub issues:
- `tunan:req` — Requirements (issue body)
- `tunan:plan` — Implementation plans (marker comment `<!-- tunan:plan -->`)
- `tunan:gate` — Acceptance gates (marker comment `<!-- tunan:gate -->`)
- `tunan:solution` — Documented solutions (marker comment `<!-- tunan:solution -->`)

A feature is **one GitHub issue** for its lifetime. There is no local-file fallback.

## Interaction Method

When asking the user a question, use the platform's blocking question tool. In Cursor, this is the `ask_user` or equivalent interactive prompt mechanism. Ask one question at a time. Prefer single-select choices when natural options exist.

When dispatching sub-agents, use Cursor's agent dispatch mechanism. Prefer bounded parallel execution where available.

